  "prompt": "What universities does CRA International recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "CRA International, formally known as **Charles River Associates (CRA)**, is a prominent global consulting firm that specializes in economic, financial, and strategic expertise. When recruiting new graduates, CRA seeks individuals who demonstrate strong analytical skills, problem-solving abilities, and the capacity to thrive in a collaborative environment.\n\n### **Universities Recruitment**\n\nCRA typically recruits from a diverse range of top-tier universities across the globe. While the specific universities may vary by region and office, they often target institutions known for their strong programs in relevant fields. Some of the universities from which CRA has historically recruited include:\n\n- **United States:**\n  - Harvard University\n  - Stanford University\n  - Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)\n  - University of Chicago\n  - Princeton University\n  - University of California, Berkeley\n  - Northwestern University\n\n- **United Kingdom:**\n  - University of Oxford\n  - University of Cambridge\n  - London School of Economics (LSE)\n\n- **Canada:**\n  - University of Toronto\n  - University of British Columbia\n  - McGill University\n\n- **Other International Institutions:**\n  - National University of Singapore (NUS)\n  - INSEAD\n  - University of Melbourne\n\nCRA also considers applications from graduates of other reputable universities, especially those with strong programs in relevant disciplines.\n\n### **Preferred Majors and Academic Background**\n\nCRA looks for candidates with academic backgrounds that demonstrate quantitative prowess, critical thinking, and analytical capabilities. Common majors and fields of study that CRA targets include:\n\n- **Economics:** Understanding of economic theory and quantitative analysis is crucial for many CRA projects.\n  \n- **Finance:** Expertise in financial modeling, investment analysis, and financial markets.\n  \n- **Mathematics & Statistics:** Strong quantitative and statistical skills are highly valued for data analysis and modeling tasks.\n  \n- **Engineering:** Problem-solving skills and technical knowledge, especially in fields like industrial or systems engineering.\n  \n- **Business & Management:** Knowledge of business operations, strategy, and organizational behavior.\n  \n- **Computer Science & Information Technology:** Skills in programming, data management, and computational analysis.\n  \n- **Political Science & International Relations:** Useful for projects involving regulatory analysis, trade, and public policy.\n  \n- **Law:** Particularly for roles that involve regulatory compliance, antitrust, and litigation support.\n  \n- **Interdisciplinary Studies:** Programs that combine quantitative and qualitative analysis, such as financial engineering or computational economics.\n\n### **Additional Qualifications and Skills**\n\nBeyond academic majors, CRA values the following in new graduates:\n\n- **Analytical Skills:** Ability to synthesize complex information and perform rigorous analysis.\n  \n- **Communication Skills:** Proficiency in conveying ideas clearly and effectively, both in writing and verbally.\n  \n- **Teamwork:** Experience working collaboratively in diverse teams.\n  \n- **Internships and Relevant Experience:** Practical experience through internships or projects can be advantageous.\n  \n- **Technical Proficiency:** Familiarity with statistical software (e.g., Stata, R), programming languages (e.g., Python, SQL), and data visualization tools.\n\n### **Application Tips**\n\n- **Tailor Your Resume:** Highlight relevant coursework, projects, and experiences that align with CRA\u2019s areas of expertise.\n  \n- **Network:** Attend career fairs, company presentations, and reach out to CRA employees on professional networks like LinkedIn.\n  \n- **Prepare for Interviews:** Be ready to discuss your analytical approach, problem-solving methods, and relevant experiences. Case interviews may also be part of the selection process.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nCRA International (Charles River Associates) seeks talented individuals from a variety of top universities with strong academic backgrounds in quantitative and analytical fields. If you're interested in pursuing a career with CRA, focus on developing relevant skills, gaining practical experience, and demonstrating your ability to tackle complex problems.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's recommended to visit [CRA\u2019s official careers page](https://www.crai.com/careers) or reach out directly to their recruitment team.",
